    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Hand gesture indicating the union of the five knowledges of the jina Buddhas into a single enlightenment. The index finger of the left hand is enclosed by the five fingers of the right hand.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000019551/Huntington, Art of Ancient India (1985)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Handgebaar dat de vereniging van de vijf wijsheden van de Dhyani Boeddha's in één verlichting aanduidt. De wijsvinger van de linkerhand wordt omsloten door de vijf vingers van de rechterhand.
</Note_Text>
